date: 2005-01-14
time: 1721
author: Justin
title: Ten Best Engines 2005

<p>
Ward's Auto has a nice <a href="http://subscribers.wardsauto.com/Microsites/index.asp?srid=10088;pageid=9608;siteid=26;magazineid=1004;srtype=1">article</a> of their 10 picks for best engines of 2005. The <a href="http://subscribers.wardsauto.com/microsites/Newsarticle.asp?newsarticleid=2737202;srid=10088;instanceid=55175;pageid=9608;magazineid=1004;siteid=26">Mazda 1.3L Renesis Rotary</a> is always an interesting one, just for the uniqueness, but my favorites are the <a href="http://subscribers.wardsauto.com/microsites/Newsarticle.asp?newsarticleid=2737201;srid=10088;instanceid=55175;pageid=9608;magazineid=1004;siteid=26">Nissan 3.5L DOHC V-6</a>, the <a href="http://subscribers.wardsauto.com/microsites/Newsarticle.asp?newsarticleid=2737207;srid=10088;instanceid=55175;pageid=9608;magazineid=1004;siteid=26">DC Mercedes 3.2L DOHC I-6 Turbodiesel</a>, and the <a href="http://subscribers.wardsauto.com/microsites/Newsarticle.asp?newsarticleid=2737210;srid=10088;instanceid=55175;pageid=9608;magazineid=1004;siteid=26">Acura 3.5L DOHC V-6</a>. My mother wants to get an Acura soonish, and that stellar engine will have me finding ways to borrow her car when she gets it. ;-)
</p>
